item.title: Believe
item.description: As a mountain endurance athlete, I’m no stranger to the concept of a challenge. My default setting is to always go a little further than I thought possible; whether its climbing higher or running further or surviving the wildest of wilderness. I always have lingering curiosity as to what lays out there. That’s how I constantly find myself in precarious situations such as butt-sliding down scree slopes, rationing water on mountain peaks or singing to bears; likely alone.
